Explanation:
As reductant hydrogen peroxide oxidises to oxygen. H2O2 → O2
​The change in oxidation number is 2
The molar mass = 34 g
Gram equivalent weight of H2O2 = (\(\frac{34}{2}\))
Equivalent weight = 152"
